derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English (denoting an administrative district): from medieval Latin praecinctum, neuter past participle (used as a noun) of praecingere 'encircle', from prae 'before' + cingere 'gird'

entry.def: A shopping precinct is an area in the centre of a town in which cars are not allowed.

entry.def: The precincts of an institution are its buildings and land.
